ntum, hold. Viscous fluid\ndynamics tends to dissipate the shear flow contribution that carries angular\nmomentum in boost-invariant fluid systems. This leads to small residual angular\nmomentum around midrapidity at late times for collisions at high energies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 May 2017 17:59:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 8 Jun 2017 20:02:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-03-14"}
